// ch11 §11.6: "an export-marked declaration only actually exports if
// it's lexically inside namespace <M1>::<M2>::...::<Mn> { ... }, where
// M1.M2. ... .Mn is exactly the current module's own dotted name." A
// single-segment module name (`foo`) maps to a single-segment namespace
// (`namespace foo { ... }`) -- the simplest case. A module's own file has
// no `main()` of its own (it's a library, not an executable), so this is
// tested from a separate, plain (non-module) consumer file that imports
// it -- exactly the shape ch11 §11.3's own examples use.
import foo;

int main() {
    return foo::helper();
}
